British Prime Minister Boris Johnson yesterday left intensive care where he had spent the three previous days for treatment against COVID-19, his Downing Street office said. “The Prime Minister has been moved this evening from intensive care back to the ward, where he will receive close monitoring during the early phase of his recovery,” said the statement. (AFP)  Coronavirus: UK prime minister moved to intensive care Boris Johnson out of COVID-19 intensive care Coronavirus intensive care -- what is involved?